      {
        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "Authorization[\"'\\s]*[:=][\"'\\s]*Bearer\\s+eyJ[A-Za-z0-9_-]{20,}\\.eyJ[A-Za-z0-9_-]{20,}\\.[A-Za-z0-9_-]{20,}",
        "message": "Ping Identity JWT Bearer token detected in Authorization header. Bearer tokens in HTTP Authorization headers provide direct API access to Ping Identity services including PingFederate admin APIs, PingAccess gateway APIs, PingOne management APIs, and federated application endpoints. These tokens authenticate API requests and grant access to sensitive identity operations such as user management, policy configuration, SSO session control, and OAuth2 resource access. Exposing Authorization header tokens enables attackers to make authenticated API calls, modify identity configurations, access user data, bypass access controls, and compromise integrated applications. Bearer tokens often have elevated privileges. Revoke exposed tokens immediately through Ping Identity console and implement secure API authentication.",
